dc:description: No 186 in the series, this rare endemic (recorded in two areas in the UK), annual or short-lived perennial ragwort, is reviewed. Morphological features are described first; additional sections cover: geographical and altitudinal distribution; habitat (climatic topographical limits and substratum); communities in which the plant is recorded; response to biotic factors; response to environment; structure and physiology; phenology; floral and seed characters; herbivory and disease; and an historical review. -S.R.Harris
